(1, 1, '2015-05-29 15:17:40', '2015-05-29 15:17:40', 'Now a days, Computer has become the most predominant machine in the world. A large number of mathematicians and programmers have added a new dimension using this indispensable machine to make our regular tasks simpler &amp; comfortable. Computer programmers translate software designs into source code in such a way that computers can accept instructions from human, perform millions of operations in a twinkling of an eye and finally visualize the calculated result in the form of human interpretative signals.\r\n\r\nIf anyone want to be a programmer, he/she must have to acquire knowledge of any programming language. There exists about 700 programming languages in the computing world. The <strong>Hello world program</strong> is the simplest program for any language that prints or displays any text message like "Hello World". Learners will get basic syntax formats for the perspective programming language quickly from this simple program. Here I will show basic syntax formats for <strong>Top 10 programming language, 2015</strong>.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Java:\r\n<pre class="theme:eclipse lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program for console output in Java">public class HelloWorld! {\r\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\r\n        System.out.println("Hello world!");\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<pre class="theme:eclipse lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program for swing output in Java">import javax.swing.JFrame;  // Importing class JFrame\r\nimport javax.swing.JLabel;  // Importing class JLabel\r\npublic class HelloWorld {\r\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\r\n        JFrame frame = new JFrame();            // Creating frame\r\n        frame.setTitle("Hi!");                  // Setting title frame\r\n        frame.add(new JLabel("Hello world!")); // Adding text to frame\r\n        frame.pack();                           // Setting size to smallest\r\n        frame.setLocationRelativeTo(null);      // Centering frame\r\n        frame.setVisible(true);                 // Showing frame\r\n        frame.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE); //Closes app on frame exit\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n<pre class="theme:eclipse lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program for applet output in Java">import java.awt.*;\r\nimport java.applet.*;\r\n\r\npublic class javaApplet extends Applet\r\n{\r\n    public void Paint(Graphics graphics)\r\n    {\r\n        graphics.drawString("Hello World", 110, 300);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n/*&lt;applet code="javaApplet.class" width=500 height=500&gt;\r\n&lt;/applet&gt;*/</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>C:\r\n<pre class="theme:vs2012 font:ubuntu-mono lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program in C">#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\r\nint main(void)\r\n{\r\n    printf("Hello world!\\n");\r\n}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>C++:\r\n<pre class="theme:vs2012 font:ubuntu-mono lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program in C++">#include &lt;iostream&gt;\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    std::cout &lt;&lt; "Hello world!" &lt;&lt; endl;\r\n}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>C#:\r\n<pre class="theme:vs2012 font:ubuntu-mono lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program in C#">using System;\r\nclass Program\r\n{\r\n    public static void Main(string[] args)\r\n    {\r\n        Console.WriteLine("Hello world!");\r\n    }\r\n}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Objective-C:\r\n<pre class="theme:vs2012 font:ubuntu-mono lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program in Objective-C">#import &lt;stdio.h&gt;\r\n#import &lt;Foundation/Foundation.h&gt;\r\n\r\nint main(void)\r\n{\r\n    NSLog(@"Hello world!\\n");\r\n    return 0;\r\n}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>PHP:\r\n<pre class="theme:sublime-text lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program in PHP">&lt;?php echo ''Hello world!''; ?&gt;</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Python:\r\n<pre class="theme:sublime-text lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program in Python">print("Hello world!")</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>JavaScript:\r\n<pre class="theme:eclipse lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program for console output in JavaScript">console.log(''Hello world!'');</pre>\r\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program for alert output in JavaScript">alert(''Hello world!'');</pre>\r\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true" title="Hello world program to show in HTML page in JavaScript">var text = document.createElement(''p'');\r\ntext.innerHTML = ''Hello world!'';\r\ndocument.body.appendChild(text);</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Ruby:\r\n<pre class="theme:sublime-text lang:default decode:true " title="Hello world program in Ruby">puts "Hello world!"</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Swift:\r\n<pre class="theme:sublime-text font:ubuntu-mono lang:default decode:true  " title="Hello world program in Swift">println("Hello world!")</pre>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Hello world!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world', '', '', '2015-07-04 22:06:09', '2015-07-04 22:06:09', '', 0, 'http://rajib.me/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 2),
