(7, 1, '2015-05-29 15:20:30', '2015-05-29 15:20:30', '<h3><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Work Experience:</strong></span></h3>\r\n<strong>Software Engineer</strong> at <strong>Eyeball International Ltd.</strong> (1<sup>st</sup> May, 2014 to Present).\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Added ffmpeg framework.</li>\r\n	<li>Added H264 Encoder &amp; Decoder.</li>\r\n	<li>Added VP8 Encoder &amp; Decoder.</li>\r\n	<li>Integrated MS-RTP Protocol to communicate with Lync 2013.</li>\r\n	<li>Converted SDP (Session Description Protocol) while SIP to WebRTC audio/video call and vice versa.</li>\r\n	<li>Implemented Passive mode DTLS-Negotiation Process for WebRTC audio/video call.</li>\r\n	<li>Enabled CABAC feature in h264 Encoder.</li>\r\n	<li>Added Google Test Framework to find crashes and bugs.</li>\r\n	<li>Created Patch to remove or add GTest Framework for ACG</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Programmer</b> at Odesk<b> </b>(Nov, 2012 to June, 2013).\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>PDF to Text to Audio Converter:</strong> Worked with TJIBEY INC. Company for this project. It was an MFC (Microsoft Foundation Class) project and developed using C++.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Nim Game:</strong> Designed algorithm to find computer’s optimized move to implement AI Strategy for this game. It was developed using Java.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Langton’s Ant:</strong> Designed algorithm of Langton''s ant movement. Langton''s ant movement is shown in this (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Langton''s_ant). Movement algorithm and Graphical user Interface was implemented using Java.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Undergraduate Thesis Work:</strong></span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Personalized delivery of content and advertisement based on client side profile management.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Ranking the Locations and Predicting Future Crime Occurrence by Retrieving News from Different Bangla Online Newspapers.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Undergraduate Project Work:</strong></span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Customized Search Engine with Web crawler and Text Match</strong>, is a desktop application that searches Journal PDF files, downloads all these pdf files, converts these PDF files into text files and finally it starts matching all these text files with user given new Journal file. Full application is created using Java, commons-io-2.4 Pdfbox-app-1.7.1, Jsoup-1.7.1, Lucene API.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Library Management System</strong> using Java and Mysql.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>File Explorer</strong> for any Operating System (Windows/Linux/Mac) using C++ and QT-SDK.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Power Explorer</strong> for Windows using Java.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Calculator</strong> using Java.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Rajib_Talkit</strong> using Java, Android SDK, TextToSpeech API in Android 2.3.6.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Funny Memo Test</strong> using Java, Android SDK, Facebook API, Adobe Photoshop in Android 4.0.3 Platform.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>5 in a Row Tic Tac Toe</strong> (30 x 30 Grid) using Java, MinMax Algorithm with AI Strategy.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Pacman</strong> using Java, BFS algorithm with AI Strategy.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tetris</strong> using C#, Multithreading.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Princess</strong> (Saving Princess from devils), using C++, Graphics.h, libbgi.a Library.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Olympic Racing</strong> using C++, Graphics.h, libbgi.a Library.</li>\r\n	<li>Clipping, Scaling, Projection, 2-D and 3-D Transformation.</li>\r\n	<li>Animation Project <strong>Aquarium</strong> (moving Fishes in Water) using Java and Graphics algorithms.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Chat Messenger combined with Tic Tac Toe</strong> Game, Server was built to manage the Whole system &amp; every clients have to send request one another through LAN or Wifi to communicate and they also can play with each other by sending game request. It is developed using Java.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Work & Experience', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'work-experience', '', '', '2015-05-31 19:44:40', '2015-05-31 19:44:40', '', 0, 'http://rajib.me/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
