(104, 1, '2015-07-23 13:57:41', '2015-07-23 13:57:41', 'Here given sample Thread implementation using C++ in Linux:\r\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true  " title="Multithread Example in Linux">/**\r\n* Author: Rajib Chandra Das\r\n* Topic: Multithread Example in Linux\r\n* Date: 6_July_2015\r\n*/\r\n\r\n#include &lt;iostream&gt; 	//For Cout/Cin\r\n#include &lt;unistd.h&gt; 	//For Usleep\r\n#include &lt;pthread.h&gt; 	//For Pthread\r\n\r\nusing namespace std;\r\n\r\n\r\nvoid *WorkerThreadFunction(void *param)\r\n{\r\n	while(true)\r\n	{\r\n		cout&lt;&lt;"Keep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;"&lt;&lt;endl;\r\n		usleep(1000000); //micro second\r\n	}\r\n}\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n	/*\r\n	* Here is the Synopsis of pthread_create Function\r\n	*\r\n	* int pthread_create(pthread_t *thread, const pthread_attr_t *attr,\r\n    *                     void *(*start_routine) (void *), void *arg);\r\n    */\r\n\r\n	pthread_t WorkerThreadHandle;\r\n\r\n	pthread_create(&amp;WorkerThreadHandle, NULL, WorkerThreadFunction, NULL);\r\n\r\n	int counter = 0;\r\n\r\n	while(true)\r\n	{\r\n		cout&lt;&lt;"Keep Alive main Thread, counter = "&lt;&lt;(++counter)&lt;&lt;endl; \r\n		usleep(3000000); //micro second\r\n		if(counter &gt; 10)\r\n		{\r\n\r\n			pthread_cancel(WorkerThreadHandle);\r\n			cout&lt;&lt;"Worker thread is closed after "&lt;&lt;counter&lt;&lt;" iteration"&lt;&lt;endl;\r\n		}\r\n	}\r\n	return 0;\r\n}</pre>\r\nHere is the command to compile and run this sample program:\r\n<pre class="theme:dark-terminal font:ubuntu-mono font-size:13 lang:default decode:true">g++ -pthread ThreadExample.cpp -o ThreadExample\r\n./ThreadExample</pre>\r\nHere is the output of this program:\r\n<pre class="theme:dark-terminal font-size:13 lang:default decode:true " title="Output of Thread Example in C++ for Linux OS">Keep Alive main Thread, counter = 1\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 2\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 3\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 4\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 5\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 6\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 7\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 8\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 9\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 10\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 11\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nKeep Alive WorkerThread------&gt;\r\nWorker thread is closed after 11 iteration\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 12\r\nWorker thread is closed after 12 iteration\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 13\r\nWorker thread is closed after 13 iteration\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 14\r\nWorker thread is closed after 14 iteration\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 15\r\nWorker thread is closed after 15 iteration\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 16\r\nWorker thread is closed after 16 iteration\r\nKeep Alive main Thread, counter = 17\r\nWorker thread is closed